<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Sushi</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Sushi rice</li>
            <li>Nori (seaweed) sheets</li>
            <li>Sushi-grade fish (tuna, salmon, etc.), sliced</li>
            <li>Vegetables (cucumber, avocado, carrot), julienned</li>
            <li>Soy sauce, for dipping</li>
            <li>Wasabi and pickled ginger, for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Sushi</li>
            <li>Japanese</li>
            <li>Seafood</li>
            <li>Rice</li>
            <li>Healthy</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Prepare sushi rice according to package instructions and let it cool to room temperature.</li>
            <li>Place a sheet of nori on a bamboo sushi rolling mat (makisu).</li>
            <li>Wet your hands and spread a thin layer of sushi rice over the nori, leaving a 1-inch border at the top.</li>
            <li>Place slices of sushi-grade fish and julienned vegetables along the bottom edge of the rice.</li>
            <li>Using the bamboo mat, roll the nori and rice over the filling, applying gentle pressure to form a tight roll.</li>
            <li>Moisten the top border of the nori with water to seal the roll.</li>
            <li>Repeat the process with different combinations of fish and vegetables to make various sushi rolls.</li>
            <li>Using a sharp knife dipped in water, slice each roll into bite-sized pieces.</li>
            <li>Serve the sushi with soy sauce, wasabi, and pickled ginger.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your homemade Sushi!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

